## Intractable Neuromuscular Blockade Resistant to Sugammadex Rescue Administration: A Case Report

The article reports a case of a patient who developed intractable neuromuscular blockade despite receiving sugammadex therapy for a brain hemorrhage. Despite immediate sugammadex administration, the patient's symptoms persisted, highlighting the challenge of treating this condition. This case underscores the difficulty in managing intractable neuromuscular blockade and emphasizes the need for further research and development of therapeutic strategies.

## India slashes GST rates to boost clean energy adoption

The Indian government has slashed the Goods and Services Tax (GST) rates on renewable energy equipment and related services, aiming to encourage clean energy adoption and reduce the country's carbon footprint. The new tax regime, effective from April 1, 2023, is expected to boost investments in renewable energy projects and contribute to achieving the country's ambitious renewable energy goals.
